{"id": "1497031596434260119", "channel_id": "1497031596434260119", "type": 0, "author_id": "706262934485073951", "author_name": "bagels5899", "author_bot": false, "content": "Reality Verges are the little globes you get every day for completing daily quests, they’re used primairly in unlocking side stories, reproduction frenzies and unlocking miscellanous things in the Archive.\n\nNow with the implementation of the handbook, players are suggested a set order in which to read the game’s story… howhever due to the way verges are structured unless you’re logging in daily and decide to do only one chapter a month there will come a point in which you simply can’t read all the stories in any given chapter section, which while a lot of these aren’t needed to understand the plot of the main story; new players likely won’t know this and those who do will just feel bad about having to skip stories especially if they were particularly invested in the story\n\nAs for solutions,  probably the most obvious one would be to outright remove the verge requirement for these stories howhever that comes with the second edge of giving the player way too many posses that they should have that early in the game. Maybe the *stories* unlock automatically as you pass by them in the handbook but you still need to pay Verges to unlock the *posses*", "timestamp": "2026-04-24T00:29:06.092000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "agree", "emoji_id": "1400771815076528258", "count": 4}, {"emoji": "♥️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 2}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1497031596434260119", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Reality Verges", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801"]}
{"id": "1497032375803318402", "channel_id": "1497031596434260119", "type": 0, "author_id": "185935184439410688", "author_name": "mirrorsara", "author_bot": false, "content": "I agree, also right now the only way to speed up story unlocks is the premium version of the curriculum pass, but time gating the story and charging money to unlock it faster is a really bad look from the perspective of new players. There are other material rewards from the pass, so it doesn't really feel like the current system is holding the story hostage or anything, but it still kind of has that appearance at first glance", "timestamp": "2026-04-24T00:32:11.908000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1497031596434260119", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Reality Verges", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801"]}
{"id": "1497032516975071456", "channel_id": "1497031596434260119", "type": 0, "author_id": "1146028256546521208", "author_name": "fleurdelyiss", "author_bot": false, "content": "just to add to this: if you only decide to unlock the stories recommended by Niko's guides, that's 60+ reality verges you need to unlock all the needed story so at least 2 months of daily logins", "timestamp": "2026-04-24T00:32:45.566000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1497031596434260119", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Reality Verges", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801"]}
